  "text": "In our previous work [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , we showed how marking the input bits using the log-likelihood ratios (LLRs) can effectively prevent failures and miscorrections resulting in a significant improvement of the iBDD performance. We referred to this approach as soft-aided bit-marking (SABM). SABM was first introduced in [CITATION_3] for staircase codes, and later also applied to PCs [CITATION_4] .",
